// ■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■
// #region Misc {						TODO: put code in a separate library

// @function  Weighted Average
// @param source	  (float) Source of series (close, high, low, etc.)
// @param length 	  (int) Period of loopback
// @param weight 	  (float) Weight
// @returns 		  (float) Series of weighted average
weightedAverage(source, weight, length) =>
	math.sum(source, length) / math.sum(weight, length)

// @function  Double smooth a value
// @param src			(float) Value
// @param firstSmoothLength	(int) First Smooth length
// @param secondSmoothLength	(int) Second Smooth length
// @param maType		(int) Type of moving average for smoothing
// @param almaOffset	(float) Offset for Arnauld Legoux Moving Average
// @param almaSigma		(float) Sigma for Arnauld Legoux Moving Average
// @param lsmaOffSet	(float) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average
// @returns             (float) Value smoothed
double_smooth(float src, simple int firstSmoothLength, simple int secondSmoothLength,
  simple int maType, simple float almaOffset=0.85, simple float almaSigma=6, simple int lsmaOffSet=0) =>

	first_smooth = MAP.getMovingAverage(typeID=maType, src=src, len=firstSmoothLength, inputAlmaOffset=almaOffset, inputAlmaSigma=almaSigma, lsmaOffset=lsmaOffSet)
	second_smooth = MAP.getMovingAverage(typeID=maType, src=first_smooth, len=secondSmoothLength, inputAlmaOffset=almaOffset, inputAlmaSigma=almaSigma, lsmaOffset=lsmaOffSet)

// @function  Measure of difference between the series and it's moving average. Same as ta.dev(), but with customized type of moving average
// @param source        (float) Series
// @param length        (int) Length for moving average
// @param maType        (int) Type of moving average for smoothing
// @param almaOffset    (float) Offset for Arnauld Legoux Moving Average
// @param almaSigma	    (float) Sigma for Arnauld Legoux Moving Average
// @param lsmaOffSet    (float) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average
// @returns 			(float) Value
dev(float source, simple int length,
  simple int maType,
  simple float almaOffset=0.85, simple float almaSigma=6,
  simple int lsmaOffSet=0) =>

    mean = MAP.getMovingAverage(typeID=maType, src=source, len=length, inputAlmaOffset=almaOffset, inputAlmaSigma=almaSigma, lsmaOffset=lsmaOffSet)

    sum = 0.0
    for i = 0 to length - 1
        val = source[i]
        sum := sum + math.abs(val - mean)

    dev = sum/length

