// ■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■
// Inverse Fisher Transform variations {

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on RSI (Relative Strengh Index).
// @param sourceRSI 	(float) Source for RSI
// @param lengthRSI 	(int) Length for RSI
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftRSI(
  float sourceRSI, simple int lengthRSI,
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	rsi = rsi(sourceRSI, lengthRSI)
	inverseFisher(rsi, lengthIFT, 50)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on ROC (Rate of Change).
// @param sourceROC 	(float) Source for ROC
// @param lengthROC 	(int) Length for ROC
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftROC(
  float sourceROC, simple int lengthROC,
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	roc = roc(sourceROC, lengthROC)
	inverseFisher(roc, lengthIFT, 0, 4)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on UO (Ultimate Oscillator).
// @param fastLength 	(int) Fast period of loopback for UO
// @param middleLength 	(int) Middle period of loopback for UO
// @param slowLength 	(int) Slow period of loopback for UO
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftUO(
  // UO settings
  simple int fastLength, simple int middleLength, simple int slowLength,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

    uo = ultimateOscillator(fastLength, middleLength, slowLength)
	inverseFisher(uo, lengthIFT, 50)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on Stochastic
// @param kLength 		(int) Period of loopback to calculate the stochastic
// @param kSmoothing 	(int) Period for smoothig stochastic
// @param dSmoothing 	(int) Period for signal (moving average of stochastic)
// @param maTypeK 		(int) Type of Moving Average for Stochastic Oscillator
// @param maTypeD 		(int) Type of Moving Average for Stochastic Oscillator Signal
// @param almaOffsetKD 	(float) Offset for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average for Oscillator and Signal
// @param almaSigmaKD 	(float) Sigma for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average for Oscillator and Signal
// @param lsmaOffSetKD 	(int) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average for Oscillator and Signal
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftStoch(
  // Stoch settings
  simple int kLength, simple int kSmoothing, simple int dSmoothing,
  simple int maTypeK, simple int maTypeD, simple float almaOffsetKD=0.85, simple float almaSigmaKD=6, simple int lsmaOffSetKD=0,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	[k, d] = stoch(kLength, kSmoothing, dSmoothing, maTypeK, maTypeD, almaOffsetKD, almaSigmaKD, lsmaOffSetKD)
	inverseFisher(k, lengthIFT, 50)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on TSI (True Strength Index)
// @param source 		(float) Source for TSI
// @param shortLength	(int) Short length for TSI
// @param longLength	(int) Long length for TSI
// @param maType		(int) Type of Moving Average for TSI
// @param almaOffset	(float) Offset for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average for TSI
// @param almaSigma		(float) Sigma for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average for TSI
// @param lsmaOffSet	(int) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average for TSI
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftTSI(
  // TSI Settings
  float source, simple int shortLength, simple int longLength,
  simple int maType, simple float almaOffset=0.85, simple float almaSigma=6, simple int lsmaOffSet=0,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	tsi = tsi(source, shortLength, longLength, maType, almaOffset, almaSigma, lsmaOffSet)
	inverseFisher(tsi, lengthIFT)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on CCI (Commodity Channel Index).
// @param source 		(float) Source for CCI
// @param length 		(int) Length for CCI
// @param maType 		(int) Type of Moving Average for CCI
// @param almaOffset 	(float) Offset for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param almaSigma  	(float) Sigma for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param lsmaOffSet  	(int) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average
// @param lengthIFT  	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftCCI(
  // CCI Settings
  float source, simple int length,
  simple int maType, simple float almaOffset=0.85, simple float almaSigma=6, simple int lsmaOffSet=0,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	cci = cci(source, length, maType, almaOffset, almaSigma, lsmaOffSet, length, maType)
	inverseFisher(cci, lengthIFT, 0, 4)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on Fisher Transform (FT).
// @param source 	  	(float) Source of FT
// @param Length 	  	(int) Length for FT
// @param lengthIFT		(int) Length for IFT
// @returns  			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftFisher(
  // FT Settings
  simple int length,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	[fisher, signal] = fisher(length)
	inverseFisher(fisher, lengthIFT, 0, 4)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on MACD (Moving Average Convergence/Divergence).
// @param source  			(float) Source of series (close, high, low, etc.)
// @param fastLength 		(int) Period for fast moving average
// @param slowLength 		(int) Period for slow moving average
// @param signalLength 		(int) Signal length
// @param maTypeFast 		(int) Type of fast moving average
// @param maTypeSlow 		(int) Type of slow moving average
// @param maTypeMACD 		(int) Type of MACD moving average
// @param almaOffset 		(float) Offset for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param almaSigma 		(float) Sigma for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param lsmaOffSet 		(int) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average
// @param lengthIFT 		(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 				(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftMACD(
  // MACD Settings
  float source, simple int fastLength, simple int slowLength, simple int signalLength,
  simple int maTypeFast, simple int maTypeSlow, simple int maTypeMACD,
  simple float almaOffset=0.85, simple float almaSigma=6, simple int lsmaOffSet=0,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

    [macd, signal, histogram] = macd(source, fastLength, slowLength, signalLength, maTypeFast, maTypeSlow, maTypeMACD,
      almaOffset, almaSigma, lsmaOffSet)

    inverseFisher(macd, lengthIFT, 0, 4)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transfor of Williams R% (Williams Percent Range).
// 		Compares the current price of an asset to its highest high and lowest low over a specified time period.
// @param source 		(float) Source of WPR
// @param length 		(int) Length for WPR
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftWPR(
  // Williams R% Settings
  float source, simple int length,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

    wpr = wpr(source, length)
    inverseFisher(wpr, lengthIFT, -50)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transfor of Williams R% (Williams Percent Range).
// @param source 	   	(float) Source of WPR
// @param length 	   	(int) Length for WPR
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftMFI(
  // MFI R% Settings
  float source, simple int length,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

    mfi = VI.mfi(source, length)
    inverseFisher(mfi, lengthIFT, 50)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transfor of CMF (Chaikin Money Flow).
// @param length 	   	(int) Length for CMF
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 			(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftCMF(
  // CMF Settings
  simple int length,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

    cmf = VI.cmf(length)
    inverseFisher(cmf, lengthIFT, 0.5)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on VO (Volume Oscillator)
// @param shortLen 		(int) Fast period for volume
// @param longLen 		(int) Slow period for volume
// @param maType 		(int) Type of moving average for smoothing
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 	 		(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftVO(
  // VO Settings
  simple int shortLen, simple int longLen,
  simple int matypeID,
  simple float almaOffset=0.85, simple float almaSigma=6,
  simple int lsmaOffSet=0,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	vo = VI.vo(shortLen, longLen, matypeID, almaOffset, almaSigma, lsmaOffSet)
	inverseFisher(vo, lengthIFT)

// @function 	Inverse Fisher Transform (IFT) on VROC (Volume Rate of Change)
// @param length 		(int) Length for VROC
// @param lengthIFT 	(int) Length for IFT
// @returns 	 		(float) Inverse Fisher Transform
export iftVROC(
  // VROC Settings
  simple int length,
  // IFT settings
  simple int lengthIFT) =>

	vroc = VI.vroc(length)
	inverseFisher(vroc, lengthIFT, 0, 4)

// #endregion
// ■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■


// ■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■■
// SMI variations {

// @function 	SMI (Stochastic Momentum Index) of RSI (Relative Strength Index)
// @param source 	  		(float) Source for RSI
// @param length 	  		(int) Length for RSI
// @param shortLengthTSI	(int) Short length for TSI
// @param longLengthTSI		(int) Long length for TSI
// @param maTypeTSI			(int) Type of Moving Average for TSI
// @param maTypeTSI			(int) Type of Moving Average for Signal of TSI
// @param almaOffsetTSI		(float) Offset for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param almaSigmaTSI		(float) Sigma for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param lsmaOffSetTSI		(int) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average
// @returns 				[float, float, float] A tuple with TSI, signal of TSI and histogram of difference
export smiRSI(
  // RSI Settings
  float source, simple int length,
  // SMI Settings
  simple int shortLengthTSI, simple int longLengthTSI,
  simple int maTypeTSI,
  simple float almaOffsetTSI=0.85, simple float almaSigmaTSI=6,
  simple int lsmaOffSetTSI=0,

  simple int maTypeSignal, simple int smoothingLengthSignal,
  simple float almaOffsetSignal=0.85, simple float almaSigmaSignal=6,
  simple int lsmaOffSetSignal=0) =>

	rsi = rsi(source, length)

	[smi, signal, histogram] = smi(rsi, shortLengthTSI, longLengthTSI, maTypeTSI, almaOffsetTSI, almaSigmaTSI,
	  lsmaOffSetTSI, maTypeSignal, smoothingLengthSignal, almaOffsetSignal, almaSigmaSignal, lsmaOffSetSignal)

// @function 	Stochastic Momentum Index of ROC (Rate of Change)
// @param source 			(float) Source for ROC
// @param length 			(int) Length for ROC
// @param shortLengthTSI 	(int) Short length for TSI
// @param longLengthTSI	 	(int) Long length for TSI
// @param maTypeTSI 		(int) Type of Moving Average for TSI
// @param maTypeTSI 		(int) Type of Moving Average for Signal of TSI
// @param almaOffsetTSI 	(float) Offset for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param almaSigmaTSI 		(float) Sigma for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param lsmaOffSetTSI 	(int) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average
// @returns 				[float, float, float] A tuple with TSI, signal of TSI and histogram of difference
export smiROC(
  // ROC Settings
  float source, simple int length,
  // SMI Settings
  simple int shortLengthTSI, simple int longLengthTSI,
  simple int maTypeTSI,
  simple float almaOffsetTSI=0.85, simple float almaSigmaTSI=6,
  simple int lsmaOffSetTSI=0,

  simple int maTypeSignal, simple int smoothingLengthSignal,
  simple float almaOffsetSignal=0.85, simple float almaSigmaSignal=6,
  simple int lsmaOffSetSignal=0) =>

	roc = roc(source, length)

	[smi, signal, histogram] = smi(roc, shortLengthTSI, longLengthTSI, maTypeTSI, almaOffsetTSI, almaSigmaTSI,
	  lsmaOffSetTSI, maTypeSignal, smoothingLengthSignal, almaOffsetSignal, almaSigmaSignal, lsmaOffSetSignal)

// @function 	Stochastic Momentum Index of VROC (Volume Rate of Change)
// @param length 			(int) Length for VROC
// @param shortLengthTSI 	(int) Short length for TSI
// @param longLengthTSI	 	(int) Long length for TSI
// @param maTypeTSI 		(int) Type of Moving Average for TSI
// @param maTypeTSI 		(int) Type of Moving Average for Signal of TSI
// @param almaOffsetTSI 	(float) Offset for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param almaSigmaTSI 		(float) Sigma for Arnaud Legoux Moving Average
// @param lsmaOffSetTSI 	(int) Offset for Least Squares Moving Average
// @returns 				[float, float, float] A tuple with TSI, signal of TSI and histogram of difference
export smiVROC(
